Title: Parallel Artificial Membrane Permeability Assay (PAMPA) 5
Description: Cell membrane permeability is important for determining oral absorption and bioavailability of drug molecule. Parallel artificial membrane permeability assay (PAMPA) is a low-cost alternative to cellular models for early ADME screening.
Interpretation: It is a classification model which returns the probability of a compound having poor permeability (>=0.5: low permeability), and the probability of a compound being highly permeable (<0.5: moderate or high permeability)
